        <abstract>
            <p>Although he believes in evolution, TM feels that natural selection is an inadequate cause;</p>
            <p>nor is he satisfied with E. D. Cope’s law of acceleration and retardation.</p>
            <p>Discusses some of his work relating to nutrition and sex and colour and sex.</p>
        </abstract>
